        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Seir also shall be a possession for his enemies.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Seir (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 32:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), or Mount Seir (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 36:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), was the old name, still retained as an alternative, of Edom. It is uncertain whether the rendering \"for his (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", Edom's) enemies\" is correct. The Hebrew is simply ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "אֹיְבָיו",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which may stand in apposition to Edom and Seir, \"his enemies,\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the enemies of Israel. So the Septuagint, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "Ησαῦ ὁ ἐχθρὸς αὐτοῦ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Shall do valiantly, or, \"shall be prosperous\" (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 8:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ruth 4:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Numbers 24:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
